reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It is new so it does cook great.
reviews.reviewText: I was really impressed with how it cooked an omelet. I usually massacre omelets and it made one no stick, no break, no mess, just beautiful and done. Anyway, I am hoping it will still do this for the life of the pan. The pan itself reminds me of cast iron but not as heavy and a lot prettier. I did have to buy a universal lid to fit the biggest pan, but I have another large pan that didn't have a lid so it had been needed. I have told others to try this pan. Musiek? is the only other I found like this and they have been out of stock for a while. I think this might be better than them as their pan lasted 6 months, but it is wait and see. Saw another review where it showed the nostick peeling, definitely not the way the Musiek pans ended. Anyway it is with everything wait and see how long the do hold up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love these. My eggs doesn't stick at all. I use margarine or lil oil for the flavors but most definitely nothing is needed when using them. Top notch cookware. Thick material but not as heavy as my cast iron. Wooden handle is strong and sturdy and never gets hot.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love, love, love, these pans!!
reviews.reviewText: These pans are sturdy and non stick and I love the way they look! I did the seasoning as the directions suggested. The non stick is wonderful! Easy to clean up even after mu husband cooks. He tends to cook on the highest setting . I can't tell you how many non stick pans I've had to smoke and rezoak after he cooks. With these pans it's a breeze to clean. Also without the cancer worries of using the traditional nonstick pans. I highly recommend

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great non stick frying pans!
reviews.reviewText: I love these frying/ sauté pans ! I use them on a glass top, electric range and they cook evenly and stay flat on the bottom. They are non stick, make the best over easy eggs and super easy to clean up! They also have great ceramic handles that don’t get hot in your hand! Probably the best pans I’ve ever used !

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I bought this pan, and a hot plate, to save money on breakfast at work. It’s working fine for that purpose, it’s light and compact. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great pan with nice features
reviews.reviewText: I bought this 8" pan to replace an old non-stick 8" pan that had become scratched. The pan arrives with the lid holder and the handle unattached to allow for a smaller package. Both were very easy to attach solidly within 1-2 minutes. The pan itself has almost vertical sides, which provides a full 8" internal diameter and allows more of whatever you're cooking in the pan. Some pans have angled sides, making the internal diameter more like 7". The pan also has 2 small pouring lips, one on each side -- a nice touch. The lid fits perfectly and has a small hole in the glass to allow pressure buildup to escape. I followed the directions and so far the pan has remained spotless and totally nonstick. The instructions don't mention dishwasher safety and I have not placed the pan in the dishwasher. The handle and lid holder look just like wood but are made of Bakelite according to the included directions. All in all a great pan and value.

I have had these for several weeks and use them almost every day. Very pleased with the quality. I no longer use oils or butter. Everything slides right off. I wasn’t sure I would be happy with purchasing something that couldn’t go in the dishwasher. These clean up fast and easy. The heat distribution is on point but does take a little bit to heat up the pan. Make sure you season them. Excellent value for the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the Netherlands on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Werkt niet op alle plekken inductie...
reviews.reviewText: Eerlijk is eerlijk, deze koekenpannen zien er echt wel top. Maar... de 2 kleinste (lichtste) pannen werken niet op elke plek van onze inductie kookplaat. Dit is voor het eerst dat dit gebeurt, eerder nooit géén probleem mee gehad met andere koekenpannen. (?) De grootste (zwaarste) werkt wel overal.

J'aime trop ces poêles:la viande est bien cuite,on n'est pas obligé de mettre trop de graisse et les patates rissolées ne collent pas au fond.En plus,c'est de la marque, que je connais pas, mais il y a logo de la marque (comme j'ai fait la photo)agréable à cuire,à tenir dans la main et à nettoyer. Maintenant, reste à vérifier pour combien de temps....mais ça peut être je demande trop à notre époque
Buenas sartenes el tiempo dirá de su durabilidad,hace poco que las tengo de momento bien
